text: Gulnor Sulaymanova (born 2 December 1990) is an Uzbekistani female kurash practitioner. She is a gold medalist at the 2017 Kurash World Championship which was held in Istanbul. She represented Uzbekistan at the 2018 Asian Games and claimed gold medal in the women's individual 52kg event. == References == Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Uzbekistani female martial artists Category:Kurash practitioners at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games gold medalists for Uzbekistan Category:Asian Games medalists in kurash
